					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wouldn't <strong>inches per second</strong> values be related to how often you read the mouse?:<br /><ul><li>If you are reading the mouse once per frame and a value of 3 appears to be 3 inches per second, then if you change to reading the mouse every other frame, a value of 3 would now represent 1.5 inches per second.</li><li>If you are reading the mouse once per frame on an NTSC system and a value of 3 appears to be 3 inches per second, then if you read the mouse once per frame on a PAL system, a value of 3 would now represent 2.5 inches per second.</li></ul><br />For comparison, nocash's <a href="http://problemkaputt.de/fullsnes.htm#snescontrollersmousetwobuttonmouse" class="postlink">fullsnes - SNES Mouse - Mouse Sensitivity</a> uses <strong>counts per inch</strong>: &quot;The Mouse Resolution is specified as '50 counts/inch (+/-10%)'&quot; (at the linear sensitivity setting).<br /><br />For the original SNES ball mouse, would it be useful to?:<br /><ul><li>Measure the diameter of the ball.</li><li>Count the number of windows on one of the encoder wheels.</li></ul></div>

